    <question><![CDATA[<p><strong>Problem solving by analogy</strong></p>

<p>You look for a similar problem that you have already successfully solved. Then you transfer the solution structure of this previous problem to the current problem. This strategy requires the ability to look beyond superficial similarities.</p>
