    <surveyls_numberformat><![CDATA[0]]></surveyls_numberformat>
    <surveyls_alias/>
    <surveyls_language><![CDATA[en]]></surveyls_language>
    <surveyls_title><![CDATA[Self-assessment questionnaire on programming strategies]]></surveyls_title>
    <surveyls_description><![CDATA[<p>Welcome to our study on the topic of “Self-assessment questionnaire on programming strategies”. We appreciate your interest and thank you for your participation. Below, we provide a brief overview of the study's content.</p>

<p><strong>Background and objective of the study</strong></p>

<p>Developing, understanding, or debugging software is a complex and highly individual process. In addition to applying specific programming techniques, programmers are constantly confronted with solving problems. Various personal strategies and approaches are used to do this. Psychology has researched and cataloged a variety of problem-solving strategies, from trial and error to goal-means analysis. However, there has been insufficient research to date on which of these basic psychological strategies programmers actually use in practice and to what extent these depend on the respective phase in the software development cycle. The aim of this study is to examine which specific strategies programmers use in different situations of the software development cycle and which of the underlying problem-solving strategies known in psychology can be assigned to these applied techniques.</p>

<p><strong>Procedure</strong></p>

<p>Once you have agreed to participate, you will be asked a few questions to help us assess your programming experience. You will then evaluate a series of statements that describe your approach to the programming process. Based on your answers, we will show you a derived profile of your problem-solving strategies (with percentages). Finally, you will evaluate the extent to which this calculated profile corresponds to your own assessment.</p>
]]></surveyls_description>
    <surveyls_welcometext/>
    <surveyls_endtext/>
    <surveyls_policy_notice><![CDATA[Participation information and privacy policy can be found at the following <a href="https://tuc.cloud/index.php/s/tSKHYBczwDBdibD">link</a>.]]></surveyls_policy_notice>
    <surveyls_policy_notice_label/>
    <surveyls_url/>
    <surveyls_urldescription/>
